The paper deals with existential rules, a formalism used in ontology-based query answering, which is a topic studied in the database (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) communities. The paper also introduces a novel approach based on derivation trees, which is a technique commonly used in logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper deals with the termination problem, which is a common problem in computer science (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
